{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1bd5a363-8098-4d3b-86f0-d6d862b8926c","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL). Migrate to `net6.0` or later.\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL). Migrate to `net6.0` or later.\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported.\n\n**Package changes in MSTest v3:**\nThe separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n\n**Recommended migration:**\n1. Update `TargetFrameworks` to replace the unsupported TFMs (e.g., `net8.0;net462`).\n2. Replace the two MSTest package references with the unified `MSTest` package (v3.x).\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8653e65d-b26e-4b0e-b9bf-a545513764a6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me assess compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 has specific minimum framework requirements. Key things to note:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks**. MSTest v3 requires at minimum:\n   - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/modern .NET)\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (this should be fine since they have net462)\n   \n   Wait, let me be more precise. \n\nMSTest v3 no longer supports .NET 5.0 or .NET Core 3.1 since both are out of support—the minimum .NET version is now 6.0. The .NET Framework 4.6.2 target will still work, but the `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets will be incompatible with MSTest v3.\n\nAdditionally, MSTest v3 consolidates the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages into a single unified `MSTest` package, so the user will need to update their package references accordingly.","outputTokens":646,"requestId":"BD0A:2DE6FB:206063C:24D3C9D:6A07DB50"},"id":"3f23a39b-405f-4134-a4be-207bdf1e1b53","timestamp":"2026-05